descript.abstract: Boundaries of Fire Safe Councils in San Diego County.
descript.purpose: This layer is a general guide for the location and boundaries of Fire Safe Councils in San Diego County.
descript.supplinf:
*Originally, these boundaries were digitized from a paper map. Geographic features and parcel lines were taken into account where possible but these boundaries should not be considered official. Call the Fire Safe Council (FSC) coordinator (see contact info) for more precise information. Several FSC boundaries follow Fire Protection District boundaries exactly. Other areas conform to CWPP (commuity wildfire protection plan) boundaries. Some FSC subchapters are shown as overlapping the principal entity or with discrete areas. This layer does not make a distinction between subchapters and the principal entity except to mention that some subchapters are not shown. Julian FSC (5 subchapters) and Scripps Ranch FSC (23 subchapters) have subchapter units that are not represented in the vector dataset.
*If no official boundary description was given in a FSC charter, then an attempt was made to estimate boundaries anecdotally or by common perception.
*FSCs are not currently organized on Native American lands with Viejas FSC being the only exception.
*Funding provided by National Fire Plan grants from the US Fish and Wildlife Service and the US Forest Service through the California Fire Safe Council.
*Thanks to Pek Pum at US FWS for his assisstance in digitizing and revising the many iterations of this dataset.
